<section class="py-24 md:py-32 border-t border-warm-border">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center mb-16">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest text-ink-muted uppercase mb-4">A brief history of PT software</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight text-ink md:text-4xl text-balance">
        Built before modern AI existed.<br />Patched, not rebuilt.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-ink-muted">
        Most personal trainer software tools were designed around drag-and-drop builders, exercise video libraries, and menu-driven workflows. That made sense in 2014. A lot has changed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-3 mb-16">

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-warm-border bg-card p-8 shadow-sm">
        <div class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-ink-muted line-through">The old way</div>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-ink-muted">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-red-400">✕</span> Open the app. Find the exercise library. Scroll. Click. Drag.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-red-400">✕</span> Format sets and reps manually. One exercise at a time.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-red-400">✕</span> Export as PDF. Hope it looks right on your client's phone.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-red-400">✕</span> Repeat for every client. Every week.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-warm-border bg-card p-8 shadow-sm flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center gap-4">
        <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-ink-muted/30 line-through">NGMI</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">Platforms built before AI existed aren't going to fix a workflow problem with a software update. They'd have to start over.</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-ink">We did.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cobalt bg-cobalt-soft p-8 shadow-sm">
        <div class="mb-4 text-2xl font-bold text-cobalt">The WAGMI FIT way</div>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-cobalt/80">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-cobalt">✓</span> Open WAGMI FIT. Type your workout the way you think it.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-cobalt">✓</span> AI structures it instantly. Exercises matched, percentages calculated.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-cobalt">✓</span> Client gets a link. Opens in any browser. No download.</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5 text-cobalt">✓</span> Done. Go coach.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-sm text-ink-muted">
      The era of clicking through exercise menus to build a program is over. <a href="#faq" class="text-cobalt hover:underline">Curious how we stack up against specific platforms?</a>
    </p>

  </div>
</section>
